==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Novelty
<hw>Nov"el*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Novelties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>novelt⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F. <ets>nouveaut⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L.
<ets>novellitas</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of
being novel; newness; freshness; recentness of origin or
introduction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Novelty</qex> is the great parent of pleasure.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something novel; a new or strange thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A small mass-produced article of little value; a
knickknack.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> knickknack.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>November</ent>⟦br⟧
